: Easiest way to do this is to simply delete them.  

: Trouble is, (unlike many think), when you delete data from your hard drive,
: it doesn't go away very easily.  The directory entries for it may be removed,
: and you may even overwrite the space with something else, but there will be 
: still magnetic traces of your data on the disks.
: The spooks have been known to
: go after your disk with a microscope and "read" the data this way (sounds 
: far-fetched, I know, but according to many folks this IS possible.)  

It should work to just overwrite it once, using random crap, or
1010101... It should all be gone.

: The only way to be 100% sure that your data is not
: read is to destroy the disk.
: (Would a high-intensity magnetic field work???)  

I am almost positive a shotgun would work. <g> Just overwrite it with
other crap...



